deck_excerpt: What would Arkana's Deck look like without changing his deck's identity? Look no further
deck_description: Keeping it simple, Keep your opponents monster to a minimum and use D Magician to beat over with help from his support cards. Traps manage problem spells and maintain D Magician. You want him out as fast as possible. Stealth bird works well with Messenger of peace in case you cannot attack with confidence. Hamon is rarely used but has potential and is mainly for defense while burning your opponent, and he can be used late game for a great burn. There can only be one is a key and VERY important. Extra deck can be experimented with but so far its been okay...same with the side deck. Don't be afraid to recommend/update this deck. I wanted to make a deck where ectoplasmer and Malice Doll of Demise would be great contributors but without changing the deck to something completely different, essentially keeping the (Arkana) soul of the deck in tact, (no pun intended, looking at you Magician's Souls).

deck_excerpt: A take on Pure Magistus for the Upcoming BODE format.
deck_description: Welcome to my second version of the Magistus Archetype post-BODE. (Original list: https://ygoprodeck.com/magistus-post-bode/) A lot of time has passed since my last update so here's a list to get people who are thinking of building this deck a few more lists to think about as BODE is right around the corner (4 days I believe?). Anyways this is going to be less in depth when compared to my old list since a lot of the reasonings/purpose of the cards remain the same as before. For the sake of ease, I'll be calling the Lvl4 Spellcasters with ED versions by these names (Verre for Rilliona Zoroa for Lvl4 Zoroa.) Likewise, the ED monsters are Rilliona for the XYZ and Daimon for Zoroa Synchro.  Description:  Magistus is a Spellcaster focused deck that focuses on the younger versions of your favorite spellcaster monsters.  List Time:  Magistus Engine (19 Cards - 12 Monsters 7 Spells)  Starters: Rilliona, Zoroa, Endymion  Extenders: Vrtira, Crowley, Trismagistus  3x Rilliona, the Magistus of Verre: The S/T Searcher for the deck. One of the 9 Starters (and the arguably worst one). It is the typically the target to search off Artemis if you already have Crowley in hand for followup.  3x Zoroa, the Magistus of Flame: Tuner of the deck. Serves as a starter as it can special summon another lv4 spellcaster from your hand/gy or attach Artemis to get to Crowley if you have spellcaster handtraps.  3x Endymion, the Magistus of Mastery:  Starter that gets to Artemis and allows you to cycle through your deck.  3x Crowley, the Magistus of Grimores:  Extender for the deck and typically the first choice of monster to grab off Artemis. His ability to change attributes comes up if you have two Crowleys on board for Rilliona XYZ (who needs two separate attributes) and for Toadally Awesome.  3x Vritra: Another extender which revives a Magistus from the GY. Typically the card you'll grab from Verre on your  3x Trismagistus: Serves as a soul charge and extender for monsters stuck in hand. Has battle protection for your Magistus monsters that are Equipped with an equip card.  1x Magistus Theurgy: Brought down from the two that I used to run. It's a nice card to have in hand/start off with but mostly serves as a way to make Rilliona a starter by itself.  Serves as an extender against Imper/Veiler for any of the starters. Can also flip in Game 1 if you equipped the wrong cards to Zoroa.  Generic Cards: x21  Hand-Traps: Droll & Lock Bird, Effect Veiler, Infinite Impermanence  3x Droll & Lock and 3x Veiler are really interesting HTs as they are also spellcasters. Going first opening multiple of drolls or uneeded veilers is fine as Crowley can discard these cards to special himself out.  3x Infinite Impermanence- I choose to run this to combat the upcoming meta however this is up to you and what you choose to run. It's a solid Hand-Trap either way as it counteract cards like TTT.  3x Pot of Desires: Draw 2 with all the important cards being 3 ofs. What more can I say?  2x Spell Power Mastery: Another 2 copies of Endymion. Adds to the consistency of this deck.  3x Triple Tactics Talents: A super strong going second or going first card. If you can't afford this feel free to run more handtraps.  1x Called by the Grave: Self-Explanatory card. Can negate a Hand-trap/card your opp uses.  3x Solemn Strike - A personal tech choice that I have. Strike is a really strong card to counteract your opponent and makes the Tenyi Swordsoul Matchup easier (Negates Vishuda).  Side Deck: (Modify to your locals)  Notable Cards are specifically Invocation and Secret Village of the Spellcasters.  Invocation is in the side rather the main deck as it's honestly a brick in the hand. Through my testing, I felt as making Aiwass was a waste of resources as it isn't a real proper negate and typically people side in backrow hate against Zoroa, so making Aiwass is less then worth it. That being said, It's sided for matchups that do not use the ED.  Secret Village - Best card of generic spellcaster support. Negates spell cards that your opponent has. Feel free to main it as well :).  Extra Deck: (going to just copy this from my old post)  2x Artemis - the best equip card that the deck has. It allows the search for any of our Magistus monsters that we need in hand.  1x Ninanruru - Our S/T removal other then cosmic. Can be useful to force activation of cards. Also has a nifty effect to allow two attacks on monsters.  1x Vahram - The main target to equip to Zoroa. Gives Zoroa a construct-like send and S/T protection. Also has a boardwipe effect that burns all face-up cards. Just like the fiery bird it is.  1x Aiwass - Our target for Fusion matchups. Can also be made with Invocation in matchups that don't use the ED. Don't forget the atk/def gain effect to hit over monsters.  2x Rilliona - Typically the card that allows the search for baby Zoroa. Allows us to consistently go into Zoroa. Remember that this card locks us into Magistus ED monsters. Also has a neat effect to negate a monster on your turn.  1x Zoroa, the Magistus of Daimon - Our main t1 board usually revolves around him. Important to realize that Zoroa says the cards don't have to be attached to him to do the floodgate effect and that Zoroa works no matter where the ED monster attempts to activate. Also has a neat reincarnation effect that becomes useful for plays later on and to reestablish the lock. Can be ran at 1 or 2 - up to your preference.  1x Bahmaut Shark/1x Toadally Awesome - fans of this deck already knows about these cards. You typically make this with Endmyion and Crowley (by changing Crowley to water). Another play to play around Nibiru or to have another negation on the board.  1x Halq/Selene/Accesscode - Standard Accesscode link climb combo. Make Halq with Zoroa and another monster then SS Veiler. Then link into Selene and revive another spellcaster. Then go into Accesscode. Typically the play that you will do to end the game.  1x Heartland Draco/Zeus: Heartland Draco has the ability to be able to attack directly to go into Zeus. Zeus is Zeus - a strong quick effect board wipe.  Anyways, I hope you guys enjoy the list and happy dueling!

deck_excerpt: Scrap Dino Ogdoadic 40 card deck with synergies that work and a lot of fun.
deck_description: I've always liked the Dinosaur deck since the release of Animadorned Archosaur and after it received indirect Scrap Raptor support for me the deck reached its peak and would not have any more innovation possible. With the July 21 banlist I thought it was really cool having to reinvent how the deck works having to do Psy-Framelord Omega to return the Miscellaneousaurus to the GY on the opponent's SP but I wasn't yet comfortable with how the deck could play against interactions and have a satisfying grind game because I'm a combo player who prefers to take advantage plays with good follow ups and minimal interactions to ensure I survive the opponent's turn and win the game easily on the back than someone who likes to put multiple negates in the table with an ftk field and the deck was missing something so I decided to stop playing with it until I found a new way to make the deck extend plays efficiently after hand traps. Now I bring you the solution I found which was to use the Archetype of Ogdoadic as an engine to complement the strategy and I am very happy with the synergies I found between the two engines. As you can see in the decklist I'm using a very reduced Dino engine because I don't want to brick with this deck and the Ogdoadic cards already improve my Grind Game a lot so I'm worried about increasing this number and the only card I'd really like to having space to use on the main deck is Pankratops but for now I'm testing it on the side deck. The Ogdoadic engine is also reduced and I chose to use only the cards necessary for its basic functioning and which has synergy with the Dino engine cards as well. Finally there was still room for 8 tech cards which is a number that guarantees seeing at least 1 hand trap in the starting hand most of the time and I've already tested a lot using blind second cards like Triple Tactics Talents and Forbidden Droplet and I say that besides being a lot of guys i often analyze replays of matches i play and if they were hand traps instead they would have been much more effective, of course there are decks where you use a hand trap and he keeps playing as if nothing had happened but most of the time a well given hand trap does affect a lot of the opponent's plays. Not to mention that this deck can use the best hand trap in the game in my opinion which is the PSY-Framegear Gamma in the main deck and the Infinite Impermanence I use instead of the Effect Veiler because first you don't use much tech card and Impermanence is a live Trap if you give it 6th card draw which Veiler is not and although I have Chaos Ruler in Extra Deck I have better cards to add to the hand like Tyranno or Oviraptor than I mill to gy. Finally about the extra deck I'm satisfied at the moment with the choices made and I just miss not having room for another generic Rank 4 like Castel, the Skyblaster Musketeer. Overall I wouldn't add any more cards for Links monsters and the Rank 8 engine and I'm testing Borreload Savage instead of Evolzar Laggia because in the grind game it's very easy to do and helps a lot to have a more solid win condition . As this deck has little room for tech and Ogdoadic's cards are a plus for the opponent if he has monsters in the GY so I always play first differently from other versions of Dino I used and I'm doing a lot of testing hands so I can see all the possibilities to extend plays after hand traps which is the purpose of the deck: pass with a field that guarantees you to survive the opponent's turn with versatile interactions and very good follow ups. The basic deck combo is to do the standard Scrap Dino moves like Oviraptor + Baby, Misc + Baby, Archosaur + Baby, Lost World + Oviraptor etc and the first extra deck monster you make is Evolzar Dolkka most of the time already guaranteeing you play around Nibiru and other random hand traps that are bad against Dino's engine but good against other deck engines like Ghost Belle. Then you access the Ogdoadic engine through the King of the Feral Imps and that's where comes why this engine works in the deck but for that I'll explain this story of the standard combo in more detail: Oviraptor + Baby = Misc + Baby = Archosaur + Baby = Oviraptor + Misc In any of these combos you will get the following board: Oviraptor + Baby + Scrap Raptor + Archosaur (or Linkuriboh in the case of the Archosaur + Baby combo) + Double Evolution Pill in the Hand Now we are going to do the sequence: Scrap Raptor eff target itself --- Scrap Raptor gy effect to add Chimera ---NS Scrap Chimera and effect --- SS Scrap Raptor and make Evolzar Dolkka using Scrap Raptor and Oviraptor as material --- after you must do Linkuriboh because even if you don't need it to banish from gy with the Double Evolution Pill it is important because it has the Dark attribute to be banned by Chaos Ruler. Then you Link Summon Scrap Wyvern with Linkuriboh and Chimera and make the standard Scrap Raptor summon from the deck and destroy the Babycerasaurus that will bring the Giant Rex. Here you can choose to play safe and make King of the Feral Imps to add Nauya to your hand because he is the best starter of the Ogdoadic engine. Or go for a more aggressive play and do Chaos Ruler which aims to get mill o Nauya or Nunu or any combination of Aleirtt + any Reptile monster. Using the example of King of the Feral Imps after adding Nauya to the hand we will use his effect and send Keurse to the GY and that way the basic Ogdoadic combo can happen with Keurse taxing the King of the Feral Imps and bringing back Nauya to the field for the second effect which will add the Ogdoadic Water Lily to the hand and we will use that to send Aleirtt to the GY. Finally Aleirtt will tax the banished Nauya and enter the field activating the second very important effect of returning two banished monsters to the gy including a Reptile monster so we will return the Miscellaneousaurus to the gy in our turn and make Number 38 or Dingirsu with both level 8 bodies on the field and now we use the Double Evolution Pill to bring Tyranno to the field and Giant Rex back to be the monster to be destroyed with Tyranno's effect. The final board will be: Tyranno + Dolkka + Giant Rex + Scrap Wyvern + Number 38 or Dingirsu. Most of the time I choose Number 38 as the final board but Number 68 is also very good and Dingirsu i make in the first turn when you know you are facing trap decks because the way a trap deck breaks your field is by destroying your cards and Dingirsu prevents this from happen. This combo is unorthodox and you can try other ways to do it because while Chaos Ruler has the advantage of being used as xyz material and you may not need to add a Reptile to your hand depending on how good the mills are but add Oviraptor for the hand for example what does it mean to be an extra body in the grind game and have Oviraptor to follow up in hand or do the combo via King of the Feral Imps which allows you to access more Ogdoadic names in the GY which makes your own Grind Game on the part of this much better engine. But we can also do simpler combos like Nunu + any Lv4 Dino = I:P Masquerena + Aron. This combo is interesting because you can risk opening with Giant Rex or Miscellaneousaurs + Nunu you use the two effects of Nunu and you will have her on the field when you give NS Dino Lv4 and you continue with King of the Feral Imps combo like me already I mentioned but here how you will have done I:P Masquerena when activating the Ogdoadic Water Lily you will have 4 Reptiles in the GY so you can reborn a Reptile to the field in the resolution and that will be Aron, the Ogdoadic King who will be able to use his two effects on opponent's turn being one of discarding a card from his hand after he adds something and another of adding a Reptile from the deck or gy to the hand if he sees an opponent's monster being sent to the gy such as when he does Link Summon and this is important because you will have Knightmare Unicorn discard cost paid without using other cards from your hand or discarding another card from your hand but at least having a normal summon next turn to make Ogdoadic plays again. In other words, this end board seems little but it's actually decent to do. Other combos I noticed with the deck: Nauya + any monster = Number 97 or Number 38. This is good if for example you give NS Ovirapor and the opponent denies it to extend moves and pass with something that guarantees you to survive. Snake Rain + Discard = Numeron Dragon OTK and Ogdoadic Spell/Trap in Hand Or Snake Rain + Discard = I:P Masquerena + Aron - exactly the same combo as Nunu + any Lv4 Dino only changing the beginning as you don't need to spend Normal Summon which means if your opponent clears your field a single Snake Rain will be or a Rank 8 or that I:P Masquerena + Aron combo. Scrap Raptor = Rank 8 - Here you can extend a little Scrap Raptor play to access some Ogoadic cards and pass with an Rank 8 and good Ogdoadic names in the GY. Archosaur + Giant Rex or Miscellaneousaurus = Rank 8. In this example instead of adding the Double Evolution Pill you add Nauya and make the default Nauya + any monster combo. Oviraptor + Double Evolution Pill = Tyranno + Rank 8 + Misc in GY - Again we are going to use the Archosaur to add the Nauya to the hand but this time we need the Double Evolution Pill to get a Reptile out of the GY before using the effect of Aleirtt to return Misc to the GY and that way we make a decent pitch while keeping a lot of great follow ups. Oviraptor + Baby + Nunu Combo with the Chaos Ruler ROTA = Tyranno + I:P Masquerena + Aron + Number 38 - Here you open with Combo plus Nunu and as this Oviraptor will most likely take hand trap it makes sense to ensure you have some play starting using Nunu's two effects and that way you are obliged to start the combo by doing King of the Feral Imps however the only difference on the end board will be that you don't have access to the Giant Rex unless you mill it with Chaos Ruler eff. In this combo you will be able to make Chaos Ruler using a Scrap Raptor and a Nauya that will be reborn with Keurse and this Chaos Ruler comes back from the gy to make a Rank 8. Oviraptor + Baby + Nunu Combo with the Borreload Savage ROTA = Tyranno + I:P Masquerena + Borreload Savage + Rank 8 - Here you do Savage instead of Chaos Ruler but I prefer the other final board because Chaos Ruler as part of your follow up is really good. Oviraptor + Baby + Nauya Combo with Chaos Ruler ROTA = Tyranno + Dolkka + Wyvern + I:P Masquerena + Number 38 - These combos you play as Dino normally having access to Dolkka on the end board different from the combo made with Nunu so you get a lot more interactions. Ovirapor + Baby + Nauya Combo with Borreload Savage ROTA = Tyranno + Dolkka + Borreload Savage + Number 38 Snake Rain + Scrap Raptor = I:P Masquerena + Bagooska /in GY: Chaos Ruler + all the Ogdoadic names /in Hand: Search of Chaos Ruler - Again this Chaos Ruler will be done after summoning Nauya with Keurse and after doing I:P Masquerena you will have the Scrap Chimera on the field so the spell Ogdoadic Water Lily will summon from any lv4 Reptile to make Bagooska. Snake Rain + Oviraptor the 3 possible situations: First: Archosaur add Double Evolution Pill and make Linkuriboh + I:P Masquerena /in Hand: Double Evolution Pill + Ogdoadic Water Lily /in GY: Misc + 3 ogdoadic names Second: add Misc and don't use it and passes with I:P Masquerena + Aron /in Hand: Ogdoadic Monster added with King of the Feral Imps + Miscellaneousaurus. Third: Use Archosaur to add an Ogdoadic name and pass with I:P + Bagooska /in GY: Misc and all the Ogdoadic names. This combo is also possible if the Snake Rain discard is a Reptile so you can add the Pill straight to the hand which is much better. These were the ideas I had so far about synergies between the deck's engines and I consider this a deck with potential because it has several different lines of play that help a lot against hand traps and in the grind game.

deck_excerpt: Lose on purpose on the first turn.
deck_description:
The ideia is to lose in the first turn. As a OTS it's not good, the opponent would just block your actions with their setup.
  • Draw your deck until you have Temple of the Kings and Wall of Revealing Light, that way you can activate the trap right at the first turn and pay 8000 LP
  • You must summon Royal Magical Library as soon as possible and activate the maximum number of spell cards you can while it's on the field.
  • Use Allure of Darkness and Dark World Dealing to discard the monster cards
  • Use Foolish Burial Goods to send Cursed Bamboo Sword from the deck to the Graveyard to add to your hand the Bamboo Sword card you need.
I think i build this deck in 2019, the banlist changed since then and i don't remember the deck exactly, i used a recorded replay of the deck in use to build this one, so you need to adjust the quantity of the cards. Adjust by adding more of one our removing one of the copies of one.

deck_excerpt: Starting with Legendary Decks II and adding retrained cards, with card drawing and searchers to evoke the heart of the cards.
deck_description:
This deck uses the Legendary Decks II Yugi deck as a base. I checked every DM episode and movie appearance of Yugi's cards on the YuGiOh Wiki, cataloging in Excel the number of duels/battles each card was used in. (Uses included seeing a card in Yugi's hand, but didn't include only seeing a card during deck-building.) Wanting to keep the Exodia pieces in the list, I chose some of the cards he used most often, selecting retrained versions where applicable. I focused Yugi's deck to have a lot of card draw and search effects to evoke the feeling of the heart of the cards.
For those that want to know the stats:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4pdLwd5QvTc Simply put: its a meme deck that i got off of an mkohl40 video taken to its logical conclusion: ritual tuners and synchro borgar. What started as a 40 dollar budget deck (that apparently beat Invoked Shaddolls and got 5th place in a 30 man tourney) has evolved into a link/syncho/ritual deck that can support even Cyber Slash Harpie Lady, Baronne de Fleur and Borrelsword Dragon.   While I went about adjusting the extra deck, i realized that i could technically go into links if I were using tokens and Linkuriboh, so I've gone ahead and done that. Magikeys are also used in order to run synchro monsters in this deck.   You have to be really careful when going about summoning your monsters because your Impcantations lock up your extra deck while there's even a single one on the board. As long as you know how to do basic addition and subtraction, you'll get the hang of it.   EDIT 1: Vanity's Fiend is an OP monster in this deck, lmao   EDIT 2: This deck sucks going second, so i tried to alleviate that as much as I could. You could probably get away with running a 42 card deck by taking out one of the Droplets (to be honest, you can also run Dark Ruler No More if price is an issue), but i highly recommend running the 3 Nibiru and 3 Re-Spark since Stardust Dragon gives you extra negates while also serving as a body on the field. But yeah, i had to throw something in there to stop monsters like Dragoon since they can cut your turn short.   EDIT 3: The deck list speaks for itself. I've decided to add Deskbot/Halqifibrax support into it. While i normally don't like to use Halqifibrax (since i like to build more casual decks), its honestly a necessity in this deck when it comes to applying real pressure. Other than that, i've taken out the Resparks (you could also run Dark Ruler No More as opposed to Droplets if money is an issue), and i've moved stuff like Vanity and Nibiru to the side deck.   EDIT 4: I've embraced the fat deck strategy after seeing a Magikey Megalith build on mkohl40's channel. After having done this, my hand consistency has gotten a lot better. It also helps that I'm running Magikey World and the PSY-Framelord Gamma kit in here now, along with 3 copies of Prosperity. Emergency Teleport can also target Penciplume, which is great for getting ritual monsters out of the graveyard. In all honesty, i don't know how i'd further improve this deck. This looks complete to me, but i may find some room for optimization in the extra deck and side deck. I'm not removing the Shooting Star Dragon kit (at least not at the moment) because it's really funny that this deck can technically go into Shooting Star Dragon.   EDIT 5: Realized there was a better Shooting Star Dragon i could go into. I can also go into it using my Halqifibrax Combo assuming i can follow up with Debris Dragon in my hand to pull Candoll out of my GY and go into Stardust Dragon. Going into Cyberse Quantum Dragon is really important to me in this deck since it gives me protection, so I'd have to forego the Herald for my level 4 synchro tuner.   EDIT 6: Running Mecha Phantom Beast Coltwing in the main deck now. I also threw out the level 4 synchro tuner for Shooting Riser Dragon.   EDIT 7: So i'm probably going to stop updating this now unless new cards come out that can further improve this. I feel like i've pushed this deck as far as it can go at the moment for the non-budget build, and i've already finished making my IRL build for the Big Mac Synchro Turbo (which can be viewed here: https://ygoprodeck.com/big-mac-synchro-turbo/). If anyone has any further suggestions, feel free to comment on this page.   EDIT 8 (final edit): I thought it couldn't be done, but here it is... True Synchro Burger Turbo. This includes a pipeline that doesn't require Halqifibrax using Mare Mare. Its just very reassuring to know that this deck can operate without the need of Halqifibrax now if we ever get into a situation where its ever banned. I'll be making incremental updates to this page as i figure out the side deck, but otherwise, i think i have it all figured out now.

deck_excerpt: Floowandereezes are as visually pleasing as they are audibly repelling
deck_description:
May I just say, Floowandereeze sounds sick. Not the good kind, the actual sickness kind of sick. The having the flu and sneezing kind of sick. And while German is by many considered to be a loud and rough sounding language the German localization for this archetype sounds fantastic! Wanderbrise. Wander is pronounced like the Wanda, either the Marvel character or Wanda from the Fairly Oddparents, depending on your generation. Brise sounds like someone is trying to say cheese in their most racist Japanese accent but with a Br instead of the Ch. Anyways, with the German lesson out of the way, let's get into the archetype.   The Legendary Bird Trio... These Arctic Terns travel from the North to the South and from the South to the Nord every year. Their travel route is depicted in their Field Spell, Floowandereeze and the Magnificent Map. Upon first read it's okay, once you know how the archetype works it's strong and once you get to know the deck it's isane. It turns any Floowandereeze into a starter, gives you an extra Normal Summon AND allows you to combo during your opponents turn. Along the way they meet fantastical places, such as Unexplored Winds, where our bird find rest on a mountain accompanied by a most magical sunset, which allows you to send one monster you control and any card your opponent controls for a Tribute Summon. Truly a magical sunset. Our friends also find shelter in the most dreamiest of towns. Here they allow you to conduct a Normal Summon and Book of Moons your opponent's entire board upon Tribute Summoning. Dreamy. The scary sea is scary so let's not talk about it. (It's a really good card but a little too win more in this tightly packed deck to justify it's inclusion)   ...The friends they meet along the way... Each of the Floowandereeze Birds has the effect that if it leaves the field face-up it gets banished instead and if you Normal Summon a Winged Beast adds itself back to hand (sounds like a lot of chainblocking and you'd be right, it is). They each have an effect that triggers upon their Normal Summon which then allows you to Normal Summon one Winged Beast monster.
  • Robina searches a Level 4 or lower Winged Beast
  • Eaglen searches you a Level 7 or higher Winged Beast
  • Strich banished a card from either players GY
  • Toccan adds a banished Floowandereeze card (card not monster. I only now got that)
Finally they meet Empen, a super cute penguin. Empen kind of works the same. Upon Summon they add you a Floowandereeze Spell or Trap to hand and then allows you to Normal Summon any monster (this will come up later). He reduces the ATK of the monster it's battling and functions as a Floodgate against Link Monsters. Mist Valley Apex Avian, a literal winged beast, and Raiza the Mega Monarch, a winged beast without wings and a chicken head, are your boss monsters. Then there's DD Crow. This crow's a pacifist and despises murder, therefore it travels alone. If you already have access to Eaglen, which is usually the case past turn one or when you using the Field Spell, this is a great card to add off of Robina. The plan is to summon Robina to search Eaglen who then searches Empen to then adds you Dreaming Town. When summoning Empen you can add your Level 1 bird back to hand to do this all over again during your opponent's turn, this time summoning either Avian or Raiza.   ...AND DIVINE WRATH. Well this took a turn for the extreme. The Extra Deck really doesn't matter much in this deck, allowing for a small Dogmatika engine. I'm saying small since - oh yeah I should probably mention you can't Special Summon the turn you use any of your birds effects - you can't Special Summon and cards like Fleur and Nexus need to sit this one out. Yet strangely enough, there's a lot of synergy between this engine and the birds. Ferrijit can be sent to add Ecclesia, allowing you to draw deeper into your deck and unbricking your hand. Shuraig can search you Robina or any other Level 1 Winged Beast as long as one tri-type is banished already. Ecclesia can be Normal Summoned at the end of your combo using Empen's effect (I told you it'll come up) to search you Dogmatika Punishment for extra interruption.   Certain choices and contrivances to conjure celestial conquest If you don't know what that means don't worry, me neither. What I do know is that this deck leaves a lot of room for intricate maneuvers. Once your opponent is out of ressources Raiza can essentially Yata-Lock your opponent by stacking their deck with a bad card and bouncing Raiza ever turn. Gold Sarc allows for every Floowandereeze to start your combo by banishing Robina (or Eaglen). It also gives you an extra chainblock. Dimension Shifter can single handedly buy you a turn or win you a game. It conflicts with the Dogmatika engine but Ferrijit can rid you of D Shifter if you don't need it. If you have both the Field Spell and Dreaming Town you can conduct a Normal Summon Twice, allowing you to summon Apex Avian upon their first Normal Summon, use it's effect and then summon Apex Avian again while flipping every monster your opponent controls face-down. Dark Simorgh can shut down control decks completely and Rallis the Star Bird has 3200 ATK if you're facing a Geomathmech Final Sigma. The only other way to out Sigma is by having a Level 1 Bird left on your side of the field and one in hand or the Field Spell face-up and two birds in hand (both very common) to go into Lyrilusc - Assembled Nightingale, swing for some direct damage, overlay into a 4 material Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder and hope your opponent is forced to crash them. Everything else in the Extra Deck is more or less moo. I doesn't matter.

It is riddled with plenty of trap cards to hold you opponent back so you can bring out the big guns. A very good starting deck. Here are some strats I've picked up:

  • Use Grave Squirmer and Cloudian - Poison Cloud face-down to eradicate your opponents cards when destroyed.

deck_name: Tri-Brigade Post BODE ft. Destiny Hero
deck_description: I uploaded a tri-brigade deck not too long ago, in which I go into more detail about how the pure deck works. Anyway I found that Small World actually works really well in this deck and it can be even better with the Destiny Hero engine I included in the deck. Small World and the Destiny Hero engines that I included in the deck can be swapped for Desires/Solemn Strike/Dragoon Engine/Zeus Package or something of the sort. This deck has so much free space and is fun to see what all can fit in the deck. Currently the deck is 43 cards, and if you have any other suggestions on some other cards I would be happy to see any input in the comments. Also here are some Small World lines of play that could be used.  Gamma/Ash/Fraktall (in hand) -> Kitt (in deck) -> Rescue Cat (adds to hand)  Effect Veiler (in hand) -> Ash (in deck) -> Fraktall/Kitt/Nervall (adds to hand)  Destiny Hero Celestial (in hand) -> Fraktall (in deck) -> Kitt (adds to hand)  Psy-Frame Driver (in hand) -> Destiny Hero Dasher (in deck) -> Kitt (adds to hand)  These are the most optimal ways I have found that Small World can be used in the deck, and using Crow also has some cool interactions in the deck. Also it has the added bonus of being able to unbrick your hand if you open garnets or too many handtraps. Anyways this is my spicy version of Tri-Brigade after BODE, hope you guys enjoy.

deck_excerpt: Swordsoul build with Tenyi to special summon more monsters, be more handtrap-proof and more consistent. Going first build, only 4 handtraps main.
deck_description: Swordsoul Tenyi can make Chaofeng with Baxia which will prevent our opponent from activating any light monster effects next turn. This is very good vs DRYTRON. Swordsoul Tenyi can play through 2-3 handtraps and still end on a decent board with Fleur (Omninegate), Grandmaster (on field monster negate) and Dragite (Spell Negate).  This swordsoul build tries to SS at least one Tenyi first to go into Monk, then SS Longyuan to make Fleur, NS Taia / Mo Ye to make Grandmaster, fetch Summit, SS Moye/Taia to make Dragite. End board is Fleur, Grandmaster, Dragite. If we start with 2 Tenyis, we can make Grandmaster without a single NS. If we start with Vessel, we can also set up enough tenyis to make Grandmaster. If we get handtrapped on the NS, we can go into Tenyi Shaman LINK2 to discard and SS from GY to trigger another Swordsoul. We can use Vessel and Dragon Circle as extenders and even to chain on veiler/Imperm on Taia/Mo Ye so that we still get the tokens. Opening Dragonsword is a one card combo: add and NS Taia, make Grandmaster cl1, cl2 Taia dump Mo Ye (chainblocking ash), add Summit, SS Mo Ye from GY with Summit, make Dragite, draw 1, have 2 negates on board.  Pot of Desires is perfect in this deck because we usually do not care about banishing 10 cards, also draw 2 without compromising the Mo Ye draw is really good (Prosperity compromises the Mo Ye draw which is very bad).  Weaknesses: Token Collector: We play 2 Ghost Belle to stop token collector +1 more in side. Shenshen can help, the Duke can take care of it, Vishuda can bounce it.  Sky Striker/ Control Decks: Making Fleur with Longyuan is going -1. if we go first, we are down -1 as well. Swordsoul Tenyi is no combo deck generating tons of plus. We should side out our ash and belle, side in anti backrow cards, opt to go second to be up in card advantage. We will lose grind games vs. control decks.     This is a build for locals, not for YCS, no droplets, no tactics, no power cards that might be too risky vs. all sorts for Tier 2 / Rogue Decks.

deck_excerpt: A Legendary Ocean + Gogiga Gagagigo deck using pre-Duelists of the Abyss support!
deck_description: This is a deck built around the level 8 normal monster Gogiga Gagagigo and his level 4 counterpart Gagagigo. Being normal monsters, they are easy to cheat out from the deck using Successor Soul and Unexpected Dai respectively. Successor Soul is non-destruction removal but it requires us to tribute one of our own effect monsters and Unexpected Dai allows us enough swarming ability to make little extra deck plays. If you draw any of these normal monsters, use Moray of Greed to put them back. Citadel Whale, Legendary Fisherman II,  Sea Stealth Attack, and A Legendary Ocean form a little engine together. A Legendary Ocean lets us summon Citadel Whale with one tribute or Legendary Fisherman II with no tributes. Foolish Burial should be used on Piwraithe (A good Successor Soul sacrifice) or Citadel Whale. Arnis the Empowered Warrior can summon Glacier Aqua Madoor, who makes a dead Gogiga Gagagigo in hand useful, and is also a hand trap himself. Along with Ash Blossom, I have 4 Fire attribute monsters, allowing me to teach Frost and Flame Dragon which is a free summon with removal. Rage of Kairyu-Shin works off original levels so it is good with this deck as well, adding more removal. Dragon's Mirror lets you summon First of the Dragons which is hard to out. Reasoning can get you a big monster for free, and you have a lot of levels so it is hard for them to guess correctly. Skill Drain is good for this deck as it uses almost no monster effects on the field. Raigeki, HFD, Reborn, and Called By are all staples.  The extra deck is a toolbox that works with or without ALO's level modulation.  The new support from Duelists of the Abyss will probably make me want to redesign this deck to use the new WATER support, so I figured I'd share it before its outdated!  The side deck is a few other options: Rescue Rabbit > Unexpected Dai | Hope Harbinger > Abyssgaios | Eria > Gagagigo the Risen

deck_excerpt: An ABC build designed to compete with meta decks while also being able to go first or second in the first duel of a match without the latter option be
deck_description: This deck, an ABC build designed to go either first or second in the first duel of the match as a result of maindecking both Crossout Designator and Forbidden Droplet, primarily relies on overwhelming the opponent in the accumulation of resources by taking advantage of ABC-Dragon Buster's ability to tag out while disrupting their plays through a combination of handtrap and extra deck monster effects.  When going first, the deck can usually either end on a simple Platinum Gadget and ABC-Dragon Buster or that same combination in addition to I:P Masquerena which allows for the likes of Appaloosa, Goddess of the Bow or Underworld Goddess of the Closed World to be summoned on the opponent's turn for additional disruption. Even in the worst case scenario wherein a tagged out ABC-Dragon Buster gets negated by the likes of something like Called by the Grave, the inclusion of Mekk-Knight Crusadia Avramax allows for a powerful wall monster to be summoned that can disrupt your opponent to some degree when sent to the GY.  On your second turn, or even your first when going second depending on your hand, you're usually capable of finishing off the opponent by link climbing into Accesscode Talker through abusing the effect of C-Crush Wyvern and sequentially summoning the Knightmare monsters. The deck primarily relies on handtraps, with more traditional trap cards being sided in for subsequent games, to increase the effectiveness of Crossout Designator while simultaneously disrupting your opponent in the event of them going first. The inclusion of PSY-Framegear Gamma aids in disrupting your opponent if you're forced to go second while otherwise countering their handtraps and gaining additional advantage for yourself through the summon of PSY-Framelord Omega or a link monster on your first turn.  In order to avoid bricking, this build runs two copies of Union Driver. If you run but a single copy, you have a 12.5% chance of drawing it when going first in contrast to having a 1.28% chance of drawing both copies when running two. Drawing a lone copy of Union Driver isn't particularly terrible, either, if you have another in deck. In the absence of drawing one of your ABC monsters alongside Union Hanger in your opening hand, possessing a single Union Driver in their place still allows you to end on either ABC-Dragon Buster and I:P Masquerena or those two monsters in addition to Platinum Gadget, a choice entirely dependent on which potential handtrap you fear at the time, due to the nature of C-Crush Wyvern's effect, which only activates if you already possess a valid target to be special summoned in your hand at the time of activation, and your ability to choose whether to resolve the effect of C-Crush Wyvern or B-Buster Drake first.  The sidedeck has been built to increase your chances of victory when going first through incorporating powerful trap cards. Said side deck also features additional handtraps that further increase the viability of Crossout Designator when going first or better disrupt your opponent when going second. Ghost Belle & Haunted Mansion also has the added benefit of protecting your cards from the likes of D D Crow, Ally of Justice Cycle Reader, and even Called by the Grave in addition to better disrupting your opponent depending on their deck.  With that said, I am interested in any suggestions pertaining to the main, side, or extra deck especially as the metagame evolves.

deck_excerpt: A deck using the Burning Abyss archetype
deck_description: This deck, I will admit, was a little bit weird to make. The main problem I had when structuring this deck was the fact that I mainly use Burning Abyss monsters as quick little card destruction effects. For example, you can special summon any Burning Abyss monster from your deck if you control no spell/trap cards. However, if you control a monster that isn't a Burning Abyss monster, the Burning Abyss monster on the field that has just been summoned gets destroyed. However, this is where you can activate their effects. My favorite card to use in a non-Burning Abyss deck is Farfa, Malebranche of the Burning Abyss, because it lets you banish one of your opponent's monsters until the end phase. All the other Burning Abyss cards have similar effects, but there's only a select few that don't use Burning Abyss monsters. Now, when using a deck that is complete Burning Abyss monsters, you will have to wait for your opponent to activate your monster's destruction effect. Is it bad that you will have to sacrifice a couple of monsters to have a chance to get out your extra deck? Yes, but when you do get your boss monsters out, it'll be HELL for your opponent. *badum* *crash*

With Adamancipator's tuner cards all excavating 5 and special summoning a rock, there are no real combos you can use. As such, learning the deck comes with a lot of trial and error, so I would suggest importing any rock deck into a simulator and doing test hands until you can relatively consistently end on good boards. A good end board will end on Crystron Halqifibrax (makes Desert Locusts to force your opponent to pitch 1, then you can make any level 10/12 synchro you like, in this deck: Geomathmech Final Sigma), Adamancipator Risen - Dragite, Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon, and Abyss Dweller (or any r4nk of your choice). There is a general structure to turns despite there being no combos:
  1. Summon as many Adamancipator tuners as possible.
  2. Use their free +1 effects to get rocks on field.
  3. Make Admancipator Risen - Raptite and activate its effect to summon another rock.
  4. Use Admancipator Risen - Raptite and a tuner to make either Adamancipator Risen - Dragite or Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon depending on the current game state.
  5. Make Crystron Halqifibrax and make more synchros.
If you didn't draw into any tuners, making Gallant Granite to search and summon Adamancipator Researcher is the first priority, after which the turn is usually dependant on excavating good cards. If you have more money to spend unlike me consider replacing some cards with Infinite Impermenance, Baronne De Fleur, etc

deck_excerpt: A competitive deck using the all-might Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon
deck_description: Ok, this is officially the first "strategy" deck that I've ever made. There really isn't any first or last step, but I'm gonna try to at least give you guys a sense of what to do. STEP ONE: Hold out for Red-Eyes Fusion - The cards inside this deck are basically just all effects for protection. You have basically all cards that negate effects, a s@!t ton of mirror forces, and you also have Gaias and Cyber Dragons to get out some synchros using the "ghost" cards. STEP TWO: Once you have acquired Red-Eyes Fusion, get out Dragoon - I'm pretty sure this is self-explanatory STEP THREE: Win - I mean, it's dragoon. If your opponent actually finds a way to counter it, and at that three of them, your opponent deserves to win. Of course, there's another way you can play this deck. STEP ONE: Set/Summon Monsters and protect them with Mirror Force: This is just another way of holding out, but in a different way than you might think. STEP TWO: Summon Predeplant Verte Anaconda - Since this is a fusion-based deck, Verte Anaconda is an obvious staple in the deck. Get this out, then send Red-Eyes Fusion to the grave to use its effect. (To get out Dragoon of course) STEP THREE: Win - The same thing as the last strategy, your opponent shouldn't be able to counter Dragoon. Thanks for checking out this deck, and best of luck on your next duel!
Yeah, I know it technically released yesterday but who cares?

deck_excerpt: Lyrilusc variant with a Tri-Brigade engine as backup dancers. The main plays focus on Level 1 Winged Beasts instead of normal Tri-Brigade combos. This
deck_description: The main goal of the deck is doing Lyrilusc things with Tr-Brigade as a support. Your main play is trying to get to double Recital Starlings to get two searches since she is not a Hard Once Per Turn (HOPT), then overlay them into Utopic Future to go into Utopic Draco Future. This play ensures your opponent either Nibirus you during this combo, making your plays safer since Nibiru is HOPT, or you have a monster negate that you save for a Nibiru or during the end phase for your Simorgh's Special Summon to go through. Your main combo line is trying to get a Turquoise Warbler and either a Celestine Wagtail or a Cobalt Sparrow, in order to search for a Lyrilusc Spell/Trap or Level 1 WB respectively. Having these two usually guarantees your UDF combo. With the Wagtail, you want to search Bird-Call, unless you already have it, in which case you search Bird Sanctuary for the extra draw or facilitating an OTK. Normally you want to activate Bird Call when you have a Lyrilusc name that you can spare in hand, since the search is great but the extra body on field is amazing. You would normally search for Nervall first if you summoned a Sparrow, or if you went for a Wagtail, search the sparrow with the first Recital. The Wagtail play is usually the more rewarding because after you added the Sparrow, you activate bird call to search for a Sapphire Swallow, then special summon the Sparrow to get the Nervall search. Now you have a Sapphire Swallow and a Nervall in hand to special summon. The rest of the combos after UDF are really up to you, and they are too spread out and different to go into details here, which is why I highly recommend watching Sir Emanon's combo tutorials for this deck, and while our lists are different, he still has great tips, and you may change this list to your preference too! Remember, decks here are merely suggestions. At the end of the day, you're the pilot of your own deck. Good luck duelist!

deck_excerpt: An anti-OP extra deck monsters deck full of hand traps.
deck_description:
Just a deck with some hand traps and goodies.
  • Synchro: Fantastical Dragon Phantazmay + Ghost Reaper & Winter Cherries = Dragocytos Corrupted Nethersoul Dragon (an easy-to-summon beatstick of 4000 with a good twice per turn battle effect, indestructible by battle, and a power decreaser with matching burn damage.)
  • Ghost Reaper & Winter Cherries is good against OP Extra Deck monsters because you can banish the same OP Extra Deck monster card as long as you have a copy of the same monster from the opponent's Extra Deck. GRWC's effect is redundant when the opponent's Extra Deck monster is on the field so try to take the first lead so your opponent can't summon any OP Extra Deck monsters.
  • Synchro: Fantastical Dragon Phantazmay + any Ghost Girl archetype monster = Dragocytos or Baroness De Fleur.
    • Baroness De Fleur is a good negate and easy to summon because of its generic synchro material requirements. Also, It can special summon 1 Level 9 or lower monster from the GY by returning itself from the field to the Extra Deck which is a good recycler for Phantazmay as the deck is full of tuners.

deck_excerpt: Triple Engine of Despia, Shaddoll, and Dogmatika focused on recursion, power, and consistency.
deck_description:
Use your plethora of tutors in conjunction with interruption to end on one of various boards (usually El Shaddoll Construct, Number 38, Winda, and/or Quaeritus), stop your opponent from doing things, and then flood the board with enough high powered creatures that you win on the spot. The Deck is split into three interconnected engines:
  • Despia: Used to summon El Shaddoll Construct, Number 38, and Quaeritus, along with providing graveyard setup, tutoring, recursion, and a negate.
  • Dogmatika: Used as the main removal engine, with Maximus/Punishment ditching Titaniklad/N'tss/Apkallone to tutor other Dogmatika monsters, remove your opponents board, or recur Shaddoll cards from your graveyard. Other than that, Fleurdelis and Ecclesia help make Construct plays, Fleurdelis can also help with Number 38, and Ecclesia/Nadir Servant act as control extender/tutor cards to keep your game plan going.
  • Shaddoll: Other removal options in Dragon/Squamata, Combo extenders in Winda/Beast/Hedgehog/Shaddoll Fusion, and tons of recursion in Schism, Winda, Apkallone, Incarnation, and Construct. Focus on trying to Winda-Schism to create a one-sided floodgate against your opponent, and create a big enough lead to win.
  • Overall: Try and tutor as many key pieces as possible to keep your opponent from stopping you, try and stop your opponent from doing anything, and then build a massive board of creatures to OTK your opponent.
Use numerons to bring out big bois and drytrons to support, also have fun

deck_excerpt: A Galaxy-Eyes deck designed to shoot for OTK that's flexible enough to play other strategies.
deck_description:
While the goal of this deck is to aim for a OTK, it's flexible enough to continue playing if that doesn't work out.

Going Second:
You will want to go second if shooting for OTK. General strategy is to XYZ Summon Prime Photon Dragon using Galaxy-Eyes Afterglow Dragon. Detach in battle phase, and double Prime Photon's already massive ATK points.

Going First:
If going first, XYZ Summon Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lord and Starliege Photon Blast Dragon (Preferably equipped with Photon Orbital, as this will make your board state very hard to deal with)  
General Commentary:
I've been working on this deck list for the better part of 3 years. Play tested against Meta, and seen lots of trial and tribulation. While it's not the best out there, it can certainly hold its own in competitive play. This is the iteration of the deck I'm currently using. Hope you enjoy playing this as much as I have making it!

deck_name: Dragonic Curse of Gaia Knight OTK
deck_excerpt: Reminisce the glory days of Yu-Gi-Oh! with Gaia the Fierce Knight/Curse of Dragon-based deck!
deck_description:
Reminisce the glory days of Yu-Gi-Oh! with Gaia the Fierce Knight/Curse of Dragon-based OTK deck! Requirements: You must have these cards on hand.
  • Artillery Catapult Turtle
  • Any "Gaia The Fierce Knight" monster (You should have 1 "Gaia the Fierce Knight" monster different from Polar Knight and Mid-Knight Sun)
  • United We Stand
  • Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring (for negates / optional)
Method:
  1. Summon Artillery Catapult Turtle and activate its effect to tribute itself to special summon Curse of Dragon, the Cursed Dragon.
    • Another Method: If you don't have UWS in hand, set ACT during your first turn, then during your next turn, summon a monster and use it as a tribute to special summon Curse of Dragon, The Cursed Dragon.
  2. After Curse of Dragon, The Cursed Dragon is special summoned, activate its effect to add Spiral Fusion from the deck to the hand.
  3. Activate Spiral Fusion to fusion summon Curse of Dragon, The Magical Knight Dragon to the field using Curse of Dragon, The Cursed Dragon and a "Gaia The Fierce Knight" monster in your hand.
  4. Activate Curse of Dragon The Magical Knight Dragon's effect to recycle Spiral Fusion from the GY to the hand.
  5. Activate Spiral Fusion again to special summon Gaia the Magical Knight of Dragons (ATK 5200 because of the effect of Spiral Fusion that benefits all "Gaia The Dragon Champion" monsters adding 2600 ATK points) by banishing the two monsters in your GY.
    • (NOTE: DO NOT TRIGGER ITS EFFECT! Also, Gaia, The Mid-Knight Sun and Gaia, The Polar Knight can't be used as fusion material for Gaia the Magical Knight of Dragons so you should have a different "Gaia the Fierce Knight" monster in your hand.)
  6. Equip the United We Stand to Curse of Dragon, The Magical Knight Dragon to have an ATK of 3600. Now you have a total of 8800 ATK point monsters.
  7. Attack to win the duel!
Swordsoul (Nov 2021) Updated!

deck_excerpt: Boring but excellent, the Zoodiac of synchro archetypes is here!
deck_description: The main aim of the deck is to swarm the field with as many synchro monsters as possible with the help of the various 1(-ish) card synchro summons the deck can achieve. These synchro monsters can then provide vital disruption and search for other key Swordsoul cards. Due to needing minimal cards to synchro summon, this allows the deck to play many hand-traps to both stop the opponent going second on top of your synchro monsters and allow you to stop them making a huge board turn 1.  The Swordsoul monsters all have the ability to summon a "Swordsoul Token" when you eg reveal another Swordsoul in hand, discard another Swordsoul, banish a Swordsoul from your GY etc., and have many cards such as "Swordsoul of Taia" and "Swordsoul Sacred Summit" to allow the deck to combo consistently post-turn 1 and through hand-traps.  "Destiny HERO - Destroy Phoenix Enforcer" synergises with cards such as "Incredible Ecclesia, the Virtuous" to give you a new Swordsoul monster every turn, whilst also being very easy to summon and generating lots of advantage due to cards such as "Destiny HERO - Celestial" who is a draw 2 in the GY next turn.  Weaknesses: floodgates such as "Summon Limit" and "There Can Be Only One", as the deck needs multiple monsters to synchro summon; "Nibiru, the Primal Being", however this can be avoided by summoning "Baronne De Fleur" with "Swordsoul Strategist Longyuan" before summoning 5 times; "Dimensional Barrier" as this is a synchro deck.  The deck is relatively easy to play, and I hope you enjoy!

deck_excerpt: Swordsoul Pure with Enforcer, Prosperity  and more handtraps
deck_description: Going first or second.  Control Variant with good enough OTK potential.  This build uses Enforcer as he has a lot of synergy with Ecclesia (adds back in end phase), Supreme Sovereignity (triggers banish eff), is a great extender, can help to draw cards and is very accessible with 3 Fusion Destiny, 3 Pot of Prosperity, Anaconda, Link Spider.  We are not comboing off in this build, we try to avoid Nibiru, avoid Sphere Mode, Lava Golem etc. by committing less summons.  This build uses 8 handtraps: 3 Ash, 3 Imperm, 2 Droll & Lock Birds. Meta Decks want to go first, we need enough hand traps to stop them. Droll & Lock is really good against all meta decks this November 2021 format (Tri Brigade, Lyrilusc, Drytron, Dragonlink, ...).  We use gold sarc as extender (banish blackout to get a token), instant fusion as extender (SS Ansy tuner lvl 4 fusion) or vs. token collector to SS Thousand Eyes to suck him.  We main deck imperial order because we want to go first and even if we get stopped by opponent's hand traps, Imp Order will shut down many decks from OTKing us. We mainly need a Normal Summon to make our strong Synchros.     We need to keep in mind that Prosperity will not let us draw with Mo Ye, so we should go for Taia, Enforcer, not do the whole swordsoul combo in the prosperity turn.  We should keep in mind that Longyuan does 1200 burn damage, gold sarc will give us the blackout trap after 2 of our standby phases, ecclesia can add back to hand if enforcer was sent to GY, dasher can SS in draw phase, ...  Dragite should always be used to excavate. Maybe our opponent tries to neg it. We could have Nibiru in deck.        We play 1 Protos in the side deck, this wyrm is searchable with Grandmaster and the Swordsoul Emergence spell. Protos can be summoned easily and shut down Drytron completely by calling light. Light can also prevent Invoked Dogma decks from summoning ecclesia, maximus, fleurdelis, Mechaba, ...  We play Evenly Matched in the side deck because it is a very flexible out vs. most meta decks.     Weaknesses:  Nibiru, Token Collector, Droll & Lock Bird, Dimension Shifter  Sphere Mode, Lava Golem  Many handtraps stopping the build up: Imperm, Veiler, Ash, belle,...

deck_excerpt: Imagine actually using the Extra Deck.
deck_description: The only advice I can really offer is just to play how Simorghs play. If you have enough board space, then you can start using the extra deck.

This deck was build considering the banlist of 2017. This strategy can be somewhat effective even nowadays against a lot of decks, including meta decks, however competitive decks have now a lot of more consistency than the competitive decks back then, not to mention that we didnt had the handtraps/removal/negates we have today. However, back in 2017, this kind of strategy could really win against the meta, even because the banlist had cards like harpies feather duster banned, dark hole at 2, solemn judgement banned, solemn warning at 1, even thunder king rai-0h was at 2 in 2017. The idea is focused into two main strategies: The first one is based on bring zap mustung and thunder king rai-oh with ties of the brethren, and to potentialize the lockdown it uses denko sekka, contract with don thousand and anti-spell fragrance, so basically if you have these 5 cards face up on the field (and your opponent draw a spell card which at that time was very common), your opponent cant search, cant special summon during their turn (until they attack), they cant normal summon/set and they cant set or activate spell/traps (except traps from hand, which at that time the only one who could actually break this lock was evenly matched). And the second strategy is to swarm monsters on the field with pa/ma for xyz summon and gain advantage with the other members of the family. So what do you think about this strategy? Was this viable at 2017? Is this strategy still viable nowadays?

deck_excerpt: If you want to play Vampire Kingdom and not think your throwing the duel
deck_description:
Intro: Vampires are my favorite archetype in Yugioh, and it bothered me to see that once vampires got support, everyone immediately concluded to use them in zombie world even though they have their own custom field spell. While I'll admit, Vampire Kingdom sucks, I refused to believe the new support had nothing to help a Vampire Kingdom strategy. So I looked through every vampire card and tried my best to make a deck that could use Vampire Kingdom to its fullest potential (which isn't much). Through my efforts, I found that this deck plays strongest against other zombie decks due to being able to tribute them with sucker, and stealing monsters even with a zombie restrictions. What is listed below is my personal identification of all the cards I chose to use, and their purpose in the deck. After that, I describe the use of basic combos to help you get started. Unfortunately I don't list any 3 card combos since I consider that to be too unlikely to be worth spending time writing down.   ====================================================================================================================================================================================== Main Deck: (9 Cards) Combo Starters: (3x) Shiranui Solitare (3x) Uni-Zombie (3x) Vampire Ghost Ogre (14 Cards) Combo Extenders/Pieces: (3x) Vampire Familiar (3x) Vampire Retainer (1x) Vampire Grace (1x) Shadow Vampire (1x) Vampire Duke (1x) Vampire Awakening (1x) Vampire Takeover (2x) Vampire's Domain (1x) Foolish Burial (2 Cards) Turn 2+ Cards: (1x) Vampire Scarlet Scourge (1x) Vampire Fraulein (1 Card) Bricks: (1x) Glow-up Bloom (3 Cards) Vampire Bricks: (2x) Vampire Kingdom (1x) Vampire Voivode (11 Cards) Tech Card Options: (3x) Vampire Domination (3x) Crossout Designator (2x) Infinite Impermanence (2x) Ash Blossom (1x) Called by the Grave (15 Cards) Extra Deck: (1x) Immortal Dragon (1x) Herald of Arc Light (1x) Formula Synchron (1x) Divine Arsenal AA-Zeus - Sky Thunder (1x) Gaia Dragon, The Thunder Charger (1x) Dhampir Vampire Sheridan (1x) Crimson Knight Vampire Bram (1x) Yuki-Onna, The Absolute Zero Mayakashi (2x) Vampire Fascinator (1x) Vampire Sucker (1x) Avendread Savior (1x) Crystron Halqifibrax (1x) Relinquished Anima   Side Deck Vampire Tech: (1x) Vampire Vamp (1x) Vampire Sorcerer Tribute Removal: (3x) The Winged Dragon of Ra - Sphere mode (3x) Gameciel, the Sea Turtle Kaiju Monster Negation: (3x) Dark Ruler No More (3x) Forbidden Droplet Monster Removal: (1x) Corpse Dragon Lord Felgrand   ======================================================================================================================================================================================   Combos: Vampire Familiar + Vampire Retainer:
  1. Normal Summon Vampire Familiar
  2. Link Summon into Relinquished Anima
  3. Activate Vampire Familiar in grave by discarding Vampire Retainer
  4. Activate Vampire Familiar on summon to search out Vampire Duke
  5. Activate Vampire Retainer in Grave by discarding Vampire Duke
  6. Activate Vampire Retainer on summon to search out Vampire Takeover
  7. Link Summon into Vampire Fascinator
  8. Set Vampire Takeover
  Vampire Ghost Ogre + Vampire Familiar/Retainer:
  1. Normal Summon Vampire Ghost Ogre
  2. Activate Ghost Ogre's effect discard Vampire Familiar/Retainer, search Vampire Grace, Send Vampire Retainer/Familiar to Grave
  3. Activate Familiar in grave and send Vampire Grace to the grave to special summon itself
  4. Activate Familiar's effect on summon to search Shadow Vampire
  5. Activate Retainer in grave and send Vampire Ghost Ogre to the grave to special summon itself. Activate Vampire Retainer to search Vampire Takeover/Vampire Domination
  6. Banish Vampire Ghost Ogre and normal summon Shadow Vampire tributing either vampire Retainer or Familiar
  7. Activate Shadow Vampire's effect on summon and special summon Vampire Duke from your deck
  8. Activate Vampire Duke's Effect on summon and force your opponent to mill 1 monster
  9. Activate Vampire Grace's Effect in Grave to special summon itself
  10. Activate Vampire Grace's effect and force your opponent to mill 1 monster
  11. Link Summon into Vampire Sucker using Vampire Grace and Vampire Familiar/Retainer
  12. XYZ summon into Crimson Knight Vampire Bram
  13. Activate Crimson Knight's effect and special summon 1 of your opponent's monsters from their grave onto your field by detaching Vampire Duke

  4. Activate Vampire Retainer in grave and send a Vampire card from your hand to grave
  5. Activate Vampire Retainer's effect on summon to search out Vampire Takeover
  6. Synchro Summon into Immortal Dragon
  7. Activate Immortal Dragon's effect to mill Vampire Duke
  8. On Turn 2, Activate Vampire Takeover (Must be Chain Link 1), summon Duke, Force your opponent to throw away a card you KNOW they have (usually a monster). Destroy a monster they control, send Vampire Voivode to grave.
  9. If your opponent ever special summons from the Grave, activate Voivode in Grave, tributing Duke and Immortal Dragon to special summon itself.
======================================================================================================================================================================================   Notes/Tips: -I forget this all the time when I'm playing, GLOW UP BULB AND VAMPIRE FASCINATOR LOCK YOU INTO ZOMBIES. This means you cannot special summon from your opponent's grave AT ALL. You Can't use Vampire Fascinator to steal a monster or use Vampire Bram or use Dhampir Vampire Sheridan to steal. This Restriction is ONLY bypassed if your opponent is ALSO playing a zombie deck. -Vampire Vamp combos best with Vampire Sorcerer for a turn 2 play. Ghost Ogre is capable of one card comboing into Vampire Vamp if you play these 2 cards together. -Vampire Bram will summon itself back Every Standby phase if its destroyed in any way. Meaning, if your able to attack with another XYZ monster while thats on the field, you can easily make AA-Zeus with it without giving up any powerful XYZ monsters. -Vampire Bram and shadow vampire's attack disabling effect can be ignored if you use their effects on Main Phase 2. -Dhampir Vampire can steal a monster that is sent to the graveyard by any card. This can be by battle, or by a card effect or by its own effect. -Vampire Fraulein + Vampire Domain leaves you with literally no reason to not spend 3000 LP every time a monster attacks. If you get 2 Domains on field, you'll gain an additional 3k LP per attack on monsters. -In the event you draw 1 of your combo pieces, and you don't have a search target, Just search out Fraulein or Domination instead. -In the event you open with Vampire Kingdom on turn 1, activate it, then search out Vampire Awakening instead of Takeover, then either: A.  Avoid sending Vampire Duke to the grave to special summon from the deck with awakening. B.  Use awakening to special summon Scarlet Scourge from the deck and use its effect to summon Duke from the grave (to simulate Vampire Takeover's effect). -Hand traps are really annoying for this deck since a single one can ruin your play, which is why I play so many anti-hand trap cards -On turn 2, I drop all anti-hand trap andd hand trap cards for board negation cards and kaijus since I don't like running the gamble of "Maybe I'll draw a hand trap that'll stop their play". I'd rather have something that can break their board instead. I also drop 2 Vampire Dominations, Crimson Knight Vampire Bram, and Shadow vampire for more board disruption. -I recommend designing the side deck to your own preference. The only cards I would recommend for the side deck are Vampire Vamp and Vampire Sorcerer. ======================================================================================================================================================================================   Conclusion: This deck is the deck I worked the most on out of all my decks (still gets bodied by solemn judgment). I'm proud to have made this and surprised that I was able to make use of most of the vampire archetype (RIP Vampire Lord, if only you were better). Regardless, it's pretty fun to play for me. I also think my decision-making when it comes to tech cards is amateur as heck and I'm sure someone else could pick better cards than the ones I chose. I hope someone who's a better deck builder takes inspiration from my deck to make something better, (so I can take it and play it) and hopefully make people a little more interested in the side of vampires no one cares about. (Even tho vampires just got support, I still wish they got a link monster to search takeover). Thanks for reading, leave a like if you enjoyed using the deck or love vampires, or leave a comment if you have any suggestions.

deck_excerpt: Probably the most competitive way to play vampires
deck_description:
Intro: I made this months ago after the Vampire support came out, but never uploaded it cuz I haven't touched this website in literal months. The side deck is ass ngl, and the extra deck is pretty full so drop whatever you think isn't necessary for combo. Same as the last deck, you want either Shiranui Solitare/Vampire Ghost Ogre/Uni-zombie + Vampire Familiar/Retainer. There are other combos, I just can't be bothered to make and write them down. Combos: God Hand: Vampire Ghost Ogre + Vampire Familiar/Retainer
  1. Normal Summon Ghost Ogre
  2. Activate Ghost Ogre's Effect and discard Familiar/Retainer and mill Retainer/Familiar. Search out Vampire Grace
  3. Activate Vampire Familiar in grave and discard Grace to special summon Familiar on field
  4. Activate familiar's effect and search out Shadow Vampire
  5. Send Ghost Ogre to grave and to activate retainer's effect in grave
  6. Activate retainer's effect and search out Vampire Domination
  7. Link Summon into Vampire Sucker
  8. Banish Ghost Ogre from grave to tribute summon Shadow Vampire
  9. Activate shadow vampire's effect to special summon Vampire Scarlet Scourge
  10. Chain Link 1: Activate Vampire Grace in Grave to special summon itself , Chain link 2: Activate Scarlet Scourge's effect on summon to special summon Vampire Sucker
  11. Activate Sucker's effect and draw 1 card
  12. XYZ summon Grace and Scourge into Beatrice (that one fairy monster in the extra deck)
  13. activate Beatrice's effect and send Banshee from deck to grave
  14. Banish Banshee from grave to play zombie world from deck
  15. You should have 4-5 cards in hand so set whatever backrow you have (including domination) and end turn. (I wish I had an idea to do something with shadow vampire)
  16. Turn 2: During the draw phase/Standby phase, activate beatrice's effect and send doomking to from deck to grave.
  17. Standby Phase, activate doomking's effect in grave and special summon itself
  18. activate vampire sucker's effect to draw 1 card
The meh hand (I should really make a better combo for this): Shiranui Solitare/Uni-Zombie + Vampire Familiar/Retainer
  1. Normal summon Shiranui Solitare
  2. activate its effect to tribute itself to special summon Uni-zombie
  3. Activate Uni-zombie's effect to mill vampire retainer/familiar
  4. activate vampire retainer/familiar in grave and send vampire familiar/retainer to grave to special summon
  5. (if special summoned vampire retainer):
  6. activate retainer's effect to search out domain
  7. activate familiar's effect in grave and send domain to grave to special summon
  8. activate familiar's effect to search out shadow vampire
  9. Synchro Summon Uni-zombie and Vampire Retainer to summon stardust charge warrior and use its effect to draw 1 card
  10. Normal summon shadow vampire by tributing vampire familiar and activate shadow vampire's effect
  11. use shadow vampire's effect to special summon vampire grace
  12. XYZ summon Beatrice with vampire grace and stardust charge warrior.
  13. do the zombie world thing where you mill banshee on turn 1 and mill doomking during draw phase of turn 2
  14. (if special summoned vampire familiar):
  15. search out a vampire monster (doesn't matter) with familiar's effect on special summon
  16. send your searched vampire monster to the grave to activate vampire retainer's effect in grave
  17. activate retainer's effect to search out vampire desire
  18. synchro summon with vampire retainer and Uni-Zombie to make Stardust charge warrior and draw 1 card
  19. use vampire desire to change vampire familiar to a level 6 by sending vampire grace to grave
  20. XYZ Beatrice with Vampire Familiar  and stardust charge warrior
  21. do the zombie world thing where you mill banshee on turn 1 and mill doomking during draw phase of turn 2
^this combo needs work Turn 2/Side Deck: All the planned turn 2 comes from the side deck.I put the usual Nibiru and forbidden droplet in the side deck. Forbidden droplet since some of the monsters can steal opponent's monsters if they are destroyed by battle. An extra ash ghost banshee and extra zombie worlds in case your opponent is playing a deck that shreads through backrow like butter. Triple Infinite impermeance to have more hand traps. and Finally, the non generic stuff, 1 Extra Jack-o-bolan to help if your normal summon is messed up, 1 Vampire Red baron (this card is super good on turn 2, not so much turn 1), and 1 Utopia beyond to swap out with beatrice or another extra deck monster (I highly doubt any opponent will let you get beatrice's effect off after setting up a turn 1), this monster is good to beat over untargetable monsters while you don't have doomking to carry you. Conclusion: I put way less thought into this deck in comparison to my vampire kingdom deck. Also im writing this at like 12 am. If you have any suggestions, post them below, and if you like the deck, leave a like and lmk you like it by leaving a comment. thanks for reading and enjoy!

deck_excerpt: A Knightmare deck that utilize each card to it's fullest potential while staying as competitive as possible. Uses banned cards.
deck_description: This abomination is an attempt to make a true Knightmare deck; and when I say "true" I mean you have to use every card in the archetype and every support card created with them in mind. I'm gonna be honest, this deck can do some disgusting things as should be expected of banned cards, but it is not competitive in the slightest. There is no room for hand-traps or meta counter utility, we're pretty much stuck with the World Legacy support which are brick more times than not. I would like to give a tutorial of the combos, but there are so many different ways to play each hand that its kind of impossible to simplify it. I feel that this deck is incomplete and deserves a 60 card variant that can better abuse some of the more niche strategies that can't fit in this 40 card build, but for now here is a Strategy: Go first, this deck cannot go second unless your opponent does nothing. The basic idea is to to use your normal summon starters like, Venus, Girsu, Iblee to set up a basic board and use Knightmare Goblin to use a second normal summon and increase your board further. This deck has a few extenders like the World Chalice, Mekk-Knight, Parallel Exceed, Pot of Avarice, used to help link climb. And a lot of in theme World Legacy support cards to act as interruptions. Your end board will vary greatly and depends on the hand your have drawn. Sometimes you will end on a Knightmare wall immune to targeting, battle, destruction in hopes of unicorn to draw you 4-5 cards your next turn; sometimes you will end on a basic Orcust loop with two negates and an I:P Masquerena; sometimes you'll end with an Avramax with an Iblee on your opponent. There are many more boards, that I will record later. Test Hands: https://youtu.be/2CFHTKr5cuw Side Deck Because I could not fit in every card smoothly, I left them in the side deck as an optional strategy change. Monstrosity "archetype" is designed to summon World Gears Theurlogical Demiurgy which is a go second board nuke. Avida Rebuilder of Worlds can also be used to reset your extra deck. A few other World Legacy cards that could use Girsu Krawler combo, or Topological Bomber Dragon board nuke. I feel bad that I can't give a more in depth analysis, you really just have to experiment with it to figure it out.

deck_description: Instant Fusion for Restrict which can counter Ash and blossom, or for rocket for further values  Mystic mine with Rocket and lampsies can burn ur opponent down. Combo chain: Any pkid- link 1- special summon fansies-link doo-entomb pkid fusion and chain doo to search for pkid pranks- link another doo- tribute doo for any pkid and pkid fusion- pkid pranks discard the monster for a token-bark- set the fusion spell and pass. At the start of opponent's turn, tribute bark-two pkids, then fusion for butler, and now you have two instant swipes, a 3000-3000 big guy, 3 pkid monsters and all of them can't be destroyed by effects.  DPE is the plan b, it's just simply strong.  Link spider can change the tokens so you can link anaconda. Anaconda can fetch for Thunder dragon fusion for fusioning the batler, it can also banish it from grave for kaiju or fansies.
